Rating: 4
This chicken deserves a dinner party. I was worried that the ease and simplicity would make it ho-hum, as some said. Definitely not the case. It had crispy skin, moist meat, and the few ingredients and minimal prep time make it a total winner. It doesn't need butter or dijon. It doesn't need vegetables or a long list of ingredients. Do what Keller says: dry it well, salt it well, put it in a roasting pan so it cooks evenly, and leave it alone. I added some white wine to the pan juices along with the thyme and scraped the pan. Then I just poured the pan sauce over the top before serving. So good, you'll want to spoon it over each bite.

