Rating: 4
I have made this roast chicken more than than any other recipe in my weekly rotation...at least 40 times per year (!), and I have always ended up with crispy, dark golden skin. The key is to dry the chicken prior to roasting. Don't add anything else that may add steam. This recipe doesn't need the thyme.....the butter at the end....or the mustard. So easy. Don't be scared when the skin gets dark around 40 minutes....that is when the goodness begns.

