Rating: 4
Great! I like to salt the bird 12 hours in advance with a 1/2 tsp of salt in the cavity and a full tsp on the outside. I also put a sprig of rosemary inside before I truss. About 45 minutes before i put it in the oven I like to add pepper to the outside (maybe a 1/2 tsp) and also another 1/2 tsp of salt. I use kosher salt. I bake a 3.5 lb bird for about 50 minutes on a roasting rack at the bottom of the oven. I spoon off the clear juice and retain the colored, thick juice. I pour about a 1/4 cup of chicken stock (white wine if I have) into the pan and scrape to get any extra juice and chicken flavor. I add all of this and the colorful juices to a small skillet and thicken. I turn the heat off and add a small slice of butter to help thicken it up. I remove the skin before adding the gravy, because I like the skin crispy and not wet. Best roast I've had.

