Rating: 4
I used this recipe for a 4lb Ginseng fed chicken, with a few little changes. I dried the bird with paper towel inside and out, placed in a raised roasting pan breast side down. I coated the skin with 1 tsp salt and 1/2 teaspoon of pepper, and inserted a meat thermometer to ensure I cooked it through. Took 70 minutes for my bird at 450 to reach 180 F inside. At that point I took it out of the oven, flipped the bird over and broiled on Low setting for 2 minutes. BEST roast chicken I've ever made, no basting, no burning and the breast was tender and juicy. Amazing crispy skin, I feel silly I've basted and buttered chickens in the past because this was perfect. Simple really is better! We ate carved up chicken with fresh mango hedgehogs on the side :)

