Rating: 4
This recipe is delicious and I have made it many times. I have found a way around the smoke! Chop root vegetables (potatoes, sweet potatoes, parsnips, etc) and put them in the bottom of the roasting pan. The chicken drippings will fall on them making them crispy on the outside, soft on the inside - delicious! Turn the veggies 2-3 times during cooking so they don't burn on one side. You can do this quick enough that it doesn't interfere w the chicken cooking. This recipe rocks! Tonight I was lazy so used adobo seasoning with salt on the outside for the flavoring.

