Rating: 4
Results were excellent! The fast cooking method works great & I had no problems with smoking. I followed recipe exactly as written with the trussing & thyme & all. I was skeptical about cooking a chicken so 'quickly' for fear of it not cooking all the way through, but that was not a problem! I used a temperature probe jabbed deep inside the meat of the thigh. When it reached 170* I took it out of the oven to let it 'carry over cook' and let it rest for 1/2 hour to let it cook the rest of the way so that it would remain juicy. {Just Google 'Carrie over cook' if you don't' know what that term means} I find leaving a chicken in the oven until it reaches 175* overcooks & will dry out chicken. The flavor wasn't as 'unusually spectacular' as I had hoped with the butter, thyme & Dijon, the flavor was very good indeed,but it was no better of a flavor than other recipes I have for chicken. To be fair I used 'Golds' Dijon mustard which I bought for the first time and find it only tastes like 'regular brown mustard' and not like Dijon at all! I won't be buying that brand again & I will stick to Grey Poupon.Maybe the flavor would have impressed me more if I had better quality Dijon Mustard with the white wine in it. This 'method' of quick cooking the chicken is something I will continue to do in the future, perhaps with different seasonings.

