The solution to the smoke and the oven clearning? Put it on the barbeque! And do it in a "disposable" aluminum pan. (I use mine about 4 times before I dispose of it.) I've done it this way for years now (in all seasons) and the result is perfect. You obviously need to have a BBQ (with a lid) that gets this hot and a temperature gauge to monitor it. I've never looked back... I have tried all sorts of chickens - free range, corn fed, el cheapo from the local grocery and I can honestly say it doesn't matter one bit: a chicken makes it's own mind up whether it's going to be a bit dry or exceptionally juicy and tender. But it's always good!

