Rating: 4
To add vegetables to the pan is to ignore the technique used in this recipe. Vegetables add steam and while that can produce a delicious dish, it is not the same. Don't skip the thyme, mustard and butter at the end of the preparation. It is a brilliant combination. I made a compound butter with the mustard and after removing most of the fat from the hot pan, stirred in the thyme, mustard, butter and then spooned it over the chicken. A truly inspired blend of flavors.

