Rating: 3
with all these rave reviews, it feels like a heresy to give only 3 forks. i definitely give 4 forks for ease of preparation; i've made this twice with organic birds and followed the recipe exactly except for placing some sprigs of thyme and a little rosemary in the cavity, and (the second time) laying thick-cut slices of potato under the chicken. the potatoes are heavenly, and the breast, especially, is very succulent! the reason for the missing fork is that while the texture of the bird is wonderful, i would like a bit more complexity or strength of flavor. didn't try butter or mustard--not my thing--but am thinking some garlic cloves in the cavity, or scattered in the pan, or fine slices beneath the skin, and/or also using the zuni trick-- sliding 4 sprigs of herbs under the skin. that makes it more labor intensive, but i think it would be worth it. i'll also try thick-cut onions and possibly carrots next time, as others have recommended. i'm sure i'll make this recipe again, but not sure if it's my holy grail. i've just been looking at the zuni method, which a friend swears by.... :)

