Fantastic, as hundreds have already pointed out. One slight modification which has served me well: I roast the chicken first for ten minutes on one side (leg down in the pan) and then for ten on the other side before turning it breast up for the remainder. Better browning on the thighs. Use this technique for my Thanksgiving bird, too.

