Rating: 4
Here is a suggestion to avoid the 'house burning down' element of the recipe. I got this from America's Test Kitchen. Try cooking your bird on a broiler pan. Underneath the grate, place a layer of foil on the bottom(for easy clean up) and a layer of sliced potatoes which have been salted and seasoned as you like. These absorb the grease and cook while the bird does, so you don't get the same smoke. When the bird is done you can lift the foil out and scrape the potatoes off. You may want to paper towel them to absorb some grease. Delicious. (Just don't tell your cardiologist)

