Rating: 4
The BEST roast chicken I have ever made. I can't believe it's so simple. I made it pretty much exactly to plan, but we all have certain variations so I'll give you my exceptions. I purchased a 3.5 lb free-range organic chicken from Whole Foods. I have ethical and medical reasons for only buying free- range organic chicken, but you really must use them for roasting, as they actually taste like chicken. I rinsed the chicken in cold water for a few minutes and then dried it very, very thoroughly with paper towel -- with special attention to the inside of the bird. It was definitely dry. I also trussed my bird with some white dental floss (I didn't have kitchen string) which worked fine. I have never trussed a bird before, but watched a YouTube clip on the web and then it only took me three seconds to do after that. Trussing seemed key for both the flavor and juiciness. I didn't have a roasting pan, so I made it in a pie pan. I used exactly one tablespoon of Cornwall rock salt, which may be too salty for some palates. I am a confirmed salt addict, so I was very pleased. I then ground some pepper over it and sprinkled some Mrs Dash on it. I had no thyme, but the Mrs Dash was perfect. I roasted it in a 450 F oven for 50 minutes without opening the oven door. When it was done cooking I removed the bird from the oven, squeezed 1/2 lemon into the pan juices and basted it for about a minute or so. I let it rest in the pie pan for about 20 minutes

