I have been doing this for a long time now, at least one year. Sometimes I trussed, sometimes I didn't... You definitely have to, for a juicier bird. Also DON'T put anything inside the chicken cavity or beneath the skin, I've tried both and it's much better without (especially, don't mess with the skin). The smoke is not that terrible if you put the chicken on the lower part of your oven. Sometimes I've had to tent it with foil, others didn't need to. Don't know what that depends on, really.

