Rating: 4
I have made this roast chicken three times and every time the result was fantastic. The last time I made it I used an organic and hormone free chicken which we bought from a local farmers market and the result was amazing. Without a doubt your oven is going to be a mess but the end result is worth it. Also, every time I made the chicken it took more than the suggested 50 to 60 minutes. On my last try it took about 1 hour and 20 minutes. All you need is just a food thermometer to make sure your bird is done. This time I made a couple of additions to the recipe. I brushed the bird with very little extra virgin olive oil. Then I grinded some sea salt, peppercorns, and rosemary and rubbed it all over the skin. I also thinly sliced some garlic and put some under the skin and some in the cavity with a branch of fresh rosemary. The end result was fantastic and the skin was delicious and the chicken itself very moist and flavorful. This is by far the best method to roast a whole chicken.

