I used a 3.6 lb Smart chicken, and followed the directions exactly, except after I washed and dried the bird, I let it sit uncovered in the fridge for an hour or so to dry out even more, for a truly crisp skin. I also put the bird on the lowest oven rack, after reading about smoking and spattering issues experienced by others. I cooked my bird at 450 for 1.5 hours - no smoking, no messy oven, no need to cover the skin due to over-browning. It came out perfect, with clear juices, crisp, beautiful skin, and the best tasting chicken ever. I will make this over and over. Simple and delicious! What more could you ask for?

