I slice potatoes, carrots, celery & onions about 1/4" thick & place on bottom of heavy roasting pan. Put split breasts on top. "Rain" with salt & pepper. Bake uncovered for 1 hour. Let set for 10 minutes. Smear with unsalted butter. Not sure I get the mustard part. Maybe it depends on the type of mustard. No smoke, no oven mess, crispy vegies. Wonderful

Rating: 4
I made this last night; it was divine. Some other tips: if you don't have kitchen twine, you can use dental floss for the trussing -- I read this in Cook's Illustrated, tried it, and it works great. Also, after you're done, take the chicken carcass and bones and all of the innards that you took out before you cooked it, dump them in a crockpot with whatever else you have in the fridge that you want to get rid of, pour 8 cups of water over it, and let it cook on low all night. the next morning, strain the stock and put it in the fridge. after a few hours, strain the fat off the top, and voila - easy homeade chicken stock!

