Had to laugh at this "recipie" (chicken, salt, pepper, hot oven, voila!) but, as I find a good roasted chicken to be one of life's great pleasures, decided to give it a go. What bliss... there's a reason Thomas Keller is who he is. Followed the directions exactly, using what another poster described as an undistinguished supermarket chicken, 4 lbs. exactly. Wiped it dry inside + out, trussed it (first time ever), rained kosher salt and cracked black pepper over, threw some thyume sprigs in the cavity ('cause I happened to have on hand) + put in 450 degree, pre-heated oven. Set timer for 1 hour. Didn't even peek. The timer went off + I removed the most beautiful roasted bird I've ever seen. No smoke, by the way, and that's NOT because my oven was perfectly clean. The skin was crackling-crisp, and the meat was moist and perfectly done. Served with garlic mashed potatoes + fresh, sauteed asparagus. "The boyfriend", a culinary-school trained chef at a very high-end resort, admitted to being humbled. (He of the "Keller just 'ain't all that" persuasion) I left the table filled with excellent food and pride at my accomplishment. A Costco chicken has it's place, but nothing, nothing could beat this beauty.

