To Judy from NYC, you actually state in your original review exactly what you did wrong: You squeezed lemon juice all over your chicken. This is why you got a rubbery bird. The percise method here is to not "steam" the bird, which is exactly what putting lemon juice on the skin did. This is simply one of my favorite dishes in the entire world. I posted a link to it on my blog and all of the readers on my blog have made it and raved and raved. I buy my birds at Whole Foods and they come already trussed, making it even easier! I have done it with and without trussing and the results are the same. There are a million reasons that I call Thomas Keller "The Man" and this dish is one of them.

