Rating: 4
I thought this recipe was too simple to make much of a difference from my normal recipe but it was so very good. I made sure the chicken sat in the fridge for 1 hour and then placed it on the roasting rack. I put the neck and giblets into the roasting pan to augment the pan juices along with some sliced lemons. My bird was almost 5 lbs. so I cooked it for 60 minutes at the directed temperature and then cooked for an additional 15 minutes at 350 degrees. I followed other reviewers' advice and dropped the oven rack one level, foil-tented the chicken for the last half hour and my oven barely smoked. I did tilt the chicken several times to allow the juice to run out of its cavity and to drip into the pan. As for the pan gravy, I lifted out the chicken to let it rest then put the roasting pan on my stove and set it to medium high. After removing the giblets & lemon, I scraped up all those lovely brown bits, mixed in a few tablespoons of flour and added beef broth (all out of chicken broth) which made a really deep flavor to the gravy. I'll be using this recipe again and again.

