Delicious and easy!!! To the cook Judy from NYC - try this again. To be fair to you, the instructions are deceptively simple. "Rain" the salt implies using a lot. "Sprinkle" would have been more appropriate a term. Indeed, if you actually measure out 1 Tbsp and use it to salt the entire chicken, it is not so much. I think you literally "rained" the kosher salt on. Yes? This would explain the over saltiness. Regarding the greasy consistency: what kind of oven to you have? Serious question here. A piece of merde oven will ruin even the best chickens and cuts of meat. Did you really have your oven at 450 degrees? It doesn't sound like it, which would explain why your chicken didn't crisp. A cheap oven thermometer will tell the truth. It sounds like you may need to invest in a good oven.

