Rating: 4
This certainly lives up to the accolades... and I actually did this with a thawed frozen chicken and had very low expectations b/c of that. I followed the directions exactly, and had to slap my hand to keep from spreading butter or olive oil on the skin. I made sure it was very dry and just used sea salt and pepper. I did put a few sprigs of rosemary and thyme in the cavity. My chicken was closer to 5 lbs and it cooked perfectly at 450 (convection) in one hour and 15 minutes. The oven was indeed very smokey and a mess. I recommend keeping some windows open when you start and making sure your ventilation is cranking. I actually put a cookie sheet under my roasting pan to catch some of the spatters and prevent them from hitting the heating element. That seemed to help a bit and didn't impact cooking temp/time b/c I was using convection. We were in the mood for mashed potatoes, so we made gravy. Just poured off all the fat and drippings and deglazed with sherry. I then added back in defatted drippings and some broth and thickened with a butter-based roux. Added in some chopped fresh rosemary and S/P.

