4 forks! Highest rating! 4 forks! Highest rating! OK, Epicurious has not so much provided us with a recipe here, but rather an incredible COOKING METHOD. I am about to roast our, um, 5th chicken in 3 days now (usually we have a roast chicken once a month-this should tell you what a great thing we're on to here now...), based on what I've easily learned from this God-like person's instructions. Forget hours of marinating, basting, etc etc etc at lower heat--I now realise it doesn't matter!! I used to to waste hours of time marinating, basting, cooking whole chickens at lower temperatures --never again! You should just pre-heat your home oven as high as possible and blast the bird for 50 minutes, (covered the whole time with a loose V-shaped foil tent on top of it; then let it sit for 10-15 minutes after the cookiing is done! (trust me--it's difficult to get a home oven above 450-490 degrees F.--especially if you are popping the oven open fromn time to time to do side dishes in the oven at the same time). Anyway, at the end, SKIP the step where it tells you to pour the drippings over the just-cooked bird, that just makes the chicken skin less crispy. Anyway, this recipe + Roxy Music CD + wine == HEAVEN!!!! Anyway, we are again drifting off into bliss with Roast Chicken and Roxy Music and Squeeze's Greatest Hits, those of you who don't get it can just go get a george foreman grill and uselessly steam good food; please; otherwise please listen to this great Epicurious recipe

